The paper deals with algorithms and data structures for solving a problem related to geographic districting in road networks. This problem involves graph-based matching and optimization, which are typical topics in computer science. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also deals with computational geometry, as it involves shortest-path distances and planar graphs, which suggests cs.CG (Computational Geometry) as another likely sub-category. The paper also involves optimization and fairness, which suggests cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) as possible sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves the analysis of algorithms and running times, which suggests cs.IT (Information Theory) as a possible sub-category.
